# .easignore — keep the EAS Build upload context small and free of secrets.
#
# EAS Build uploads the project directory tree to its cloud. In a pnpm
# monorepo, that tree is huge (node_modules, web build artifacts, plans,
# data dumps). This file is gitignore-style — anything matched here is
# excluded from the upload.
#
# This file lives at the monorepo root, which is the upload context
# when EAS is invoked with --project-dir apps/mobile from the root, or
# if anyone runs `eas build` from the root by accident. A separate
# .easignore is also recommended at apps/mobile/ — that is the canonical
# EAS project root and is the one EAS reads by default.
#
# Owned by: DevOps (slice D, Sprint 1).

# --- Dependency trees ----------------------------------------------------
# EAS Build re-installs dependencies via pnpm using the lockfile.
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# --- Build artifacts of sibling apps ------------------------------------
# EAS is only building apps/mobile; sibling app build outputs are dead weight.
apps/web/build/
apps/web/.react-router/
apps/worker/dist/
apps/web/.cache/
apps/worker/.cache/

# --- Repo-level artifacts not relevant to the mobile build --------------
# Docs (markdown runbooks, audit reports, marketing copy) — never read by EAS.
docs/
# Mavis plan / task tree artifacts.
.mavis/
# Local data dumps (Postgres, Redis, SQLite) — bind mounts from the dev host.
data/
/data/

# --- Caches and transient state -----------------------------------------
.cache/
.tmp/
.audit/
.turbo/
.nyc_output/
coverage/

# --- VCS state ----------------------------------------------------------
# .git is huge and useless on the build machine; EAS does not need it.
.git/
.gitignore

# --- Editor / OS metadata -----------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# --- Logs ---------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
*.log.*

# --- Local env / secrets ------------------------------------------------
# Never upload secrets. EAS secrets are configured via `eas env:create`,
# not by bundling .env files.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.cer
*.mobileprovision
google-services.json
GoogleService-Info.plist

# --- Mobile-app-specific noise ------------------------------------------
# Anything generated by Expo / RN during local dev. EAS rebuilds these.
.expo/
.expo-shared/
ios/
android/
*.app.dSYM.zip
*.jsbundle
*.hbc
*.map
